SIMPLE: interjectional
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Interjectional
<hw>In`ter*jec"tion*al</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <sn>1.</sn>
<def>Thrown in between other words or phrases; parenthetical;
ejaculatory; <as>as, an <ex>interjectional</ex> remark</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Pertaining to, or having the nature of, an
interjection; consisting of natural and spontaneous
exclamations.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Certain of the natural accompaniments of <qex>interjectional</qex>
speech, such as gestures, grimaces, and gesticulations, are restrained
by civilization.</q> <rj><qau>Earle.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Interjectionalize</ent>⟦br⟧
